.TH TTS 1 "March 2025" "Dawnstar ReadAloud 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tts \- Text-to-Speech application with neural voices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tts
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fISOURCE\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tts
is a lightweight Text-to-Speech (TTS) application that reads text from files,
PDFs, EPUBs, URLs, or direct input. It features smart caching, multi-language
support (US English, UK English, Tamil), and deep system integration including
global keyboard shortcuts for reading selected text.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-lang\fR=\fILANG\fR
Language code: en-us, en-uk, ta, en, en-gb (default: en-us)
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-speed\fR=\fISPEED\fR
Speech speed: slow, normal, fast (default: normal)
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose output
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-cache\fR
Disable audio caching
.TP
\fB\-\-clear\-cache\fR
Clear the audio cache
.TP
\fB\-\-sentence\-file\fR=\fIFILE\fR
File to write current sentence for cursor tracking
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Show version information
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show help message
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Speak text directly:
tts "Hello world"
.TP
Read a file:
tts document.txt
.TP
Read a webpage:
tts https://example.com/article
.TP
Use UK English at fast speed:
tts -l en-uk -s fast "Hello world"
.TP
Clear audio cache:
tts --clear-cache
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/tts/config.yaml
User configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.cache/tts_app/
Audio cache directory
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
Ctrl+Alt+S
Speak selected text (when configured)
.TP
Ctrl+Alt+Q
Stop speaking (when configured)
